sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Platform User
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Controller as MCPServer Controller<br/>(mcp-lifecycle-operator-system)
    participant MCPPod as MCP Server Pod<br/>{spec.config.port}/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,MCPPod: Flow 1: MCPServer Reconciliation

    User->>K8s: Create/Update MCPServer CR
    K8s-->>Controller: Watch event (MCPServer change)

    Controller->>K8s: GET ConfigMaps, Secrets<br/>Bearer Token (SA)<br/>Validate references exist
    K8s-->>Controller: ConfigMap/Secret data

    Note over Controller: Compute SHA-256 config hash<br/>from referenced data

    Controller->>K8s: Create/Update Deployment + Service<br/>Bearer Token (SA)<br/>Set ownerReferences, config-hash annotation
    K8s-->>Controller: Deployment + Service created

    Note over Controller: Wait for Deployment available<br/>with healthy replicas

    Controller->>MCPPod: POST MCP initialize handshake<br/>HTTP (plaintext, in-cluster)<br/>No auth (401/403 = "reachable")
    MCPPod-->>Controller: Server info, protocol version,<br/>capabilities (tools, resources, prompts)

    Note over Controller: On failure: exponential backoff<br/>10s → 20s → 40s → 80s → 120s<br/>max 10 retries

    Controller->>K8s: PATCH MCPServer/status<br/>Bearer Token (SA)<br/>Conditions: Accepted, Ready<br/>Address URL, server info, capabilities
    K8s-->>Controller: Status updated

    Note over User,MCPPod: Flow 2: ConfigMap/Secret Rolling Update

    User->>K8s: Update ConfigMap or Secret
    K8s-->>Controller: Watch event (ConfigMap/Secret change)

    Note over Controller: Field index lookup:<br/>find MCPServers referencing<br/>this ConfigMap/Secret

    Controller->>K8s: GET all referenced ConfigMaps/Secrets<br/>Bearer Token (SA)
    K8s-->>Controller: Updated data

    Note over Controller: Recompute SHA-256 config hash

    Controller->>K8s: PATCH Deployment pod template<br/>annotation mcp.x-k8s.io/config-hash<br/>Bearer Token (SA)
    K8s-->>Controller: Deployment updated

    Note over K8s: Kubernetes triggers<br/>Deployment rolling update
